# Cloudflare Workers Assets headers.
#
# Cross-origin isolation: turns on `crossOriginIsolated`, which unlocks
# SharedArrayBuffer — required by WebR (the R cell) and @antv/layout-wasm
# (Facet 1M-node GPU layouts). `credentialless` (not `require-corp`) lets the
# app's cross-origin no-credential fetches through WITHOUT the origins needing
# to send CORP headers — critical because the deploy cross-fetches the 34 MB
# DuckDB-wasm from the GitHub Pages mirror (Cloudflare's 25 MB/file limit
# forces it off-origin). Verified: the engine boots cross-origin under these
# headers and the full smoke passes. See DECISIONS (COOP/COEP for Fork 2 R +
# Facet).
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
